
k8s test conectivity commands:

#### NetCat command from the origin pod cli:
1 - Get the IP of the destiny svc/pod: k get pod -owide / k get svc
2 - Get into the origin Pod:
	k exec -it webapp-color -- sh
3   Run netcat test:
	nc -z -v <destiny_svc> <port>
	nc -z -v secure-service 80

What you will see:

If there is NO conectivity: You will see nothing, you will need to ctrl + c to leave the command.

If there IS connectivity: You will see a message saying that is open:

/opt # nc -z -v secure-service 80
secure-service (10.102.141.135:80) open

k run tmp --restart=Never --rm -i --image=nginx:alpine -- curl 10.0.0.67

k -n mars run tmp --restart=Never --rm -i --image=nginx:alpine -- curl -m 5 manager-api-svc:4444



